00:17:41.792 --> 00:17:46.336
Wesleyan idea of perfection and it's simply loving God and loving neighbor

00:17:47.264 --> 00:17:51.840
So I hope this will maybe wet your whistle, so to speak, as my dad used to say.

00:17:52.128 --> 00:17:58.240
about what might be coming next week because these are very important topics about God's grace.

00:17:58.112 --> 00:17:59.456
In our life.

00:17:59.456 --> 00:18:01.888
and the way that we can respond to them. Amen?

00:18:02.112 --> 00:18:07.456
Let's pray. Dear God, thank you so much for your amazing gifts in our life.

00:18:07.328 --> 00:18:13.824
Thank you so much for what Jesus has done for us, what you have done through Christ.

00:18:13.568 --> 00:18:17.664
In our life, help us, Lord, to respond to you.

00:18:17.472 --> 00:18:25.568
and if we haven't god accepted you as our lord and savior through jesus we just ask god that you would fill us full.

00:18:25.344 --> 00:18:31.936
Of your spirit that even if now is not the right time that you would plant in us a seed

00:18:32.288 --> 00:18:33.792
To open the door.

00:18:33.824 --> 00:18:35.264
To your grace

00:18:35.232 --> 00:18:36.864
To your forgiveness

00:18:36.768 --> 00:18:39.168
To your reconciliation lord

00:18:39.360 --> 00:18:40.960
We love you so much.

00:18:41.056 --> 00:18:43.072
And it's in Jesus' name that we pray. Amen

00:18:43.104 --> 00:18:44.000
Amen.
